Steps to use the script: 

1. Right-click the WindowsScript file and select "Save As"
2. Save it with the name: CP-Hardening.ps1 (make sure it has the .ps1 extension)
3. Right-click on PowerShell and select "Run as Administrator"
4. Navigate to the folder where you saved the script:
   cd "C:\Path\To\Your\Script"
5. If needed, enable script execution (one time only):
   Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser
6. Run the script:
   .\CP-Hardening.ps1
7. Use the menu to select hardening options

Important: This script must be run as Administrator to work properly! 